  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "[Capella](https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/blob/dev/specs/capella/beacon-chain.md#extended-containers) and [EIP-4844](https://www.eip4844.com/) will require changes to mev-boost, builder-specs and relays.\r\n\r\nBoth introduce new fields to `BeaconBlockBody`, `ExecutionPayload` and `ExecutionPayloadHeader`: [eip4844](https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/blob/dev/specs/eip4844/beacon-chain.md#extended-containers) / [capella](https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/blob/dev/specs/capella/beacon-chain.md#extended-containers) \r\n\r\nThis breaks previous SSZ encoding/decoding (and strict JSON too), and will likely need\r\n\r\n* [ ] update builder-specs to add new `getPayloadV2` API that accepts the updated data types\r\n* [ ] update [go-boost-utils](https://github.com/flashbots/go-boost-utils) to add new versions of the types with the new fields\r\n* [ ] update to mev-boost to implement the new API with the new types\r\n* [ ] \"For the relayer side, there's more work, they probably want to verify blobs, the commitments, and the version hashes are valid. Those will be coming from the builders\" (@terencechain)\r\n\r\nQuestions: \r\n1. will this need getPayloadV2 for Capella and getPayloadV3 for EIP4844?\r\n2. how can BNs detect whether the mev-boost version supports this before signing and sending the beacon block?",
